## Public Interface

### AudioReactivity Class

```python
# src/vjlive3/audio/reactivity.py
class AudioReactivity:
    def __init__(self):
        """Initialize audio reactivity framework"""
    
    def register_effect(self, effect: AudioReactiveEffect) -> None:
        """Register an effect for audio reactivity"""
    
    def unregister_effect(self, effect: AudioReactiveEffect) -> None:
        """Unregister an effect"""
    
    def set_mapping(self, effect_id: str, parameter: str, mapping: AudioMapping) -> None:
        """Set parameter mapping for an effect"""
    
    def update(self, analysis: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:
        """Update all registered effects with new audio analysis"""
    
    def set_mood(self, mood_id: str) -> None:
        """Set current mood (changes reactivity behavior)"""
```

### AudioReactiveEffect Interface

```python
class AudioReactiveEffect:
    def __init__(self, effect_id: str):
        """Initialize effect with unique ID"""
    
    def get_parameters(self) -> Dict[str, Any]:
        """Get current parameter values"""
    
    def set_parameter(self, name: str, value: float) -> None:
        """Set parameter value"""
    
    def on_audio_event(self, event: AudioEvent) -> None:
        """Handle audio events (beat, silence, etc.)"""
```

### AudioMapping Data Structure

```python
@dataclass
class AudioMapping:
    audio_feature: str          # "bass", "mid", "high", "beat", "rms"
    parameter: str             # Effect parameter name
    mapping_type: str          # "linear", "exponential", "logarithmic", "threshold"
    min_value: float           # Minimum parameter value
    max_value: float           # Maximum parameter value
    smoothing: float           # Smoothing factor (0-1)
    activation_threshold: Optional[float] = None  # For threshold mappings
```

